</p><p class="- topic/p ">As a workaround it often helps to add the Google DNS servers in 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Network connection -&gt; Network Adapter</b> : 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">DNS server: 8.8.8.8 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">2nd DNS server: 8.8.4.4 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-48841417-37C5-4A79-8EEF-789A56E72B5A"><title class="- topic/title ">Example DNS setting</title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-A24EAD6E-A8FA-442F-9722-C662F23C9D42-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-A24EAD6E-A8FA-442F-9722-C662F23C9D42-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">.
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">In case you face SNMP or TLS errors</b>, try the following in the printer’s WebUI:
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> change the setting “minimal version of TLS protocol” to “TLSv1.2” 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> change the setting “use of less strong ciphers suites” to “Enabled”
</p></li></ul><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-D6175B7F-5625-4C4B-B3BD-DE5E90D1C4AD"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-A4B1EE81-EA95-47FE-9B7D-7A82A9698BB1-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-A4B1EE81-EA95-47FE-9B7D-7A82A9698BB1-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-DFD95E44-6FE2-4690-855D-446A64ABF90C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>ORS: On Remote Service</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
